    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Thermoplastic polyester manufactured from corn starch or other renewable resources. First developed for use as a synthetic fiber during World War 2 when organic materials were in short supply. In conservation used as a protective covering for stone materials exposed outdoors. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
